speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for War (1) whether he is aware that the Royal Northumberland Fusiliers are to receive the Honorary

Freedom of Berwick-on-Tweed on 21st April, and of Newcastle-on-Tyne on St. George's Day, and that permission to wear full-dress uniform on these two occasions has been refused in spite of the fact that full-dress uniform is available at the regimental depot for the band, the colour parties and the escorts; that this refusal has caused great disappointment to the regiment and to the general public in Northumberland, and if he will now reverse this decision;

(2) on what grounds it is laid down in A.C.I.'s and confirmed in Northern Command orders that full-dress uniform is obsolete and may not be worn by Army personnel even on special ceremonial occasions for which it was appropriate before the war.
